HEADWORD: Assot
<hw>As*sot"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>asoter</ets>, F. <ets>assoter</ets>; <?/ (L. <ets>ad</ets>) +
<ets>sot</ets> stupid. See <er>Sot</er>.]</ety> <def>To besot; to
befool; to beguile; to infatuate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some ecstasy <qex>assotted</qex> had his sense.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Assot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Assot
<hw>As*sot"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Dazed; foolish; infatuated.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Willie, I ween thou be <qex>assot</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Assuage</ent>⟦br⟧
